@node 7 " Piracy "

Please don't accept illegal copies of this program, when misc. costs are 
added, I only make just over ฃ2uk on each registration so every copy pirated
does count!

I am deliberately selling the full version at a cheap price so you have no
excuse for not registering...

This program has taken me a lot of work to complete!  This is the first time
anyone in the world has created a patch like this!  So if I see/hear of a
BBS using a pirated version of the full release, the BBS will be shut down!
Using what ever methods I think appropriate...


  *********   If a program is worth using, it is worth buying   **********

@endnode

@node 8 " Programmers comments about MAX's "

Hi

The MAX's BBS v1.54 source code is a total mess, full of out dated practices
and won't even re-assemble on modern assemblers live Devpac!!!

Most of my work involved trying to figure out what Anthony Barrett was 
trying to achieve in his programming...  Even tho he states it was written
in assembler, the code looks more like it came from a dodgy C compiler!!!

This is probably why MAX's never got past v1.54, as it would of taken him
months to fix the problems!  The GUI code is still from workbench v1.3 when
v1.54 was released in 1994 when most people had A1200's etc...

I would advise anyone else thinking of writing another patcher for MAX's not
to bother!, however, MAX's Pro does have a pointer to the original program
code so you could write plug-ins without some of the hassle I went though :)

That's all for now :)

@endnode
